			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>That would be criminal, stupid, and criminally stupid.</p>
<p>Since he was involved with response to this breach, that association with the company, whether as an employee, contractor, or temp&#8230; legally that&#8217;s an &#8220;insider&#8221;.</p>
<p>So although he could hold a position in the stock&#8230; anything like buying or short selling stock during the last few months&#8230; would immediately put him under severe liability for insider trading.</p>
<p>This isn&#8217;t the case of some outsider, blogger, or pundit making wild claims anonymously or under a pseudonym in order to move a stock.  This is someone with inside knowledge, and thus subject to strict regulations.</p>
