				<cite class="fn">Jhon </cite><a href="https://krebsonsecurity.com/2021/03/whistleblower-ubiquiti-breach-catastrophic/comment-page-2/#comment-531091"><time datetime="2021-04-02T10:16:17-04:00">April 2, 2021</time></a>			</header><!-- .comment-meta -->

			
			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>MS Authenticator also lets you sync across multiple devices.</p>
							</section><!-- .comment-content -->

			<div class="reply">
							</div><!-- .reply -->
		</article><!-- #comment-## -->
	<ol class="children">
	<li class="comment even depth-5" id="li-comment-531092">
		<article id="comment-531092" class="comment">
			<header class="comment-meta comment-author vcard">
				<cite class="fn">Jhon </cite><a href="https://krebsonsecurity.com/2021/03/whistleblower-ubiquiti-breach-catastrophic/comment-page-2/#comment-531092"><time datetime="2021-04-02T10:18:44-04:00">April 2, 2021</time></a>			</header><!-- .comment-meta -->

			
			<section class="comment-content comment">
				<p>Clarification &#8211; MS Authenticator lets you back up all of your TOTP codes to your Microsoft account, so that you can restore them to other devices. MS is storing your TOTP configuration so that you&#8217;re not required to rely on any other devices.</p>
